Digital Communications Associates Incsaid the U.S. District Court issued a ruling prohibiting&lt;Softklone Distributing Corp> from selling a software productthat Digital claimed violates one of its copyrights.    The company said no damages were set in the court's ruling.    "The court has validated our contention that the userinterface and the appearnace of a product is a vital element ofthe product and is protectable by U.S. copyright law," thecompany said.    Digital said the ruling involved a copyright infringementsuit filed against Softklone by Microstuf Inc, which Digitalacquired in October 1986.    The suit charged that Softklone's Mirror software productviolated the copyright of Microstuf's CrossTalk program,Digital said. Reuter&#3;